summary: This document is an email chain from February 2020 discussing the status of subpoenas served to multiple airlines and Expedia for travel records related to Ghislaine Maxwell. The correspondence shows prosecutors actively gathering evidence for the Maxwell case, with particular interest in Southwest Airlines records.

events.title: Deadline for airline subpoena responses
events.description: The deadline for airlines to respond to subpoenas for travel records related to Ghislaine Maxwell passed.

events.title: Subpoenas served to airlines
events.description: Subpoenas were served to United, Delta, Southwest, American, and Airline Reporting Corp for travel records.

locations: 28 Liberty Street, New York County (Manhattan), New York, New York 10005
keyFacts: Prosecutors were actively subpoenaing airline travel records in February 2020 as part of the Ghislaine Maxwell investigation.
Subpoenas were served to United, Delta, Southwest, American, Airline Reporting Corp, Alaska, JetBlue, and Expedia.
The Expedia subpoena specifically related to "Maxwell travel" indicating focus on Ghislaine Maxwell's movements.
Prosecutors expressed particular interest in Southwest Airlines records and urgency due to "timing pressure."
The email chain shows coordination between legal team members to ensure compliance with subpoena deadlines.
